><div class="t me5f x64 h27 y17a2 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who were with him? Acts 15 : 40; 16: 1-3. • </div><div class="t ma2 x18 h27 y17a3 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t mb1c x29 h27 y1afe ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is said of the importance of Philippi? </div><div class="t m2da x4 h27 y165d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 16: 12. Note </div><div class="t m1cd x18 h27 y1abc ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m8f x29 h27 y1d21 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Paul begin his labors there? Verse 13. </div><div class="t m1d0 x18 h27 y1b74 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m735 x29 h27 y1c34 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What woman accepted the gospel? Verse 14. </div><div class="t m1d2 x18 h27 y1a2c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m5aa x29 h27 y1a53 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did she show her love for the cause ? Verse </div><div class="t m300 xbd h27 y1a2d ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">15. </div><div class="t m1d5 x18 h27 y1d66 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t mf57 x29 h27 y1b1a ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As the work continued, what attempt was made to </div><div class="t ma5 x4 h27 y211c ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bring it into disrepute? Verses 16, 17. </div><div class="t m127 x18 h27 y1a9e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9. </div><div class="t m99 x29 h27 y1a9e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did the apostle put a stop to this proceeding? </div><div class="t m60c x4 h27 y64e ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verse 18. </div><div class="t me4 x16 h27 y1b3f ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. </div><div class="t m3ad x29 h27 y1eec ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Was not what the girl said the truth? Then why </div><div class="t m748 xe h27 y1378 ff4 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">did Paul rebuke her ? Note 2, </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
